1195
00:49:40,711 --> 00:49:42,612
I'm so glad you asked!

1196
00:49:42,679 --> 00:49:45,415
-He went through so much trouble.
-I'm sorry.

1197
00:49:45,482 --> 00:49:47,818
I was a bit too excited.

1198
00:49:47,884 --> 00:49:49,853
All right. I finally get

1199
00:49:49,920 --> 00:49:52,122
-why you can't tell pork and beef apart!
-I get it now.

1200
00:49:52,189 --> 00:49:53,957
-I get it.
-I finally get it.

1201
00:49:54,858 --> 00:49:57,694
That's why this is called Super Udon!

1202
00:49:58,362 --> 00:49:59,496
HE GOT IT

1203
00:49:59,563 --> 00:50:00,630
The noodles were good,

1204
00:50:00,697 --> 00:50:03,667
so he forgot and thought,
"Did I have these noodles?"

1205
00:50:03,734 --> 00:50:05,369
"Are these noodles mine?"

1206
00:50:05,435 --> 00:50:07,404
It's so good
that he's losing his memories.

1207
00:50:07,471 --> 00:50:08,739
Try the soup too.

1208
00:50:08,805 --> 00:50:10,140
A SIP OF THE SOUP

1209
00:50:10,207 --> 00:50:12,542
I got too excited,
so my hands are trembling.

1210
00:50:12,609 --> 00:50:15,412
I've never been this excited
while shooting a show.

1211
00:50:17,614 --> 00:50:19,816
-And next.
-Is this fish?

1212
00:50:19,883 --> 00:50:22,452
-He had cod fillets, so I fried those.
-Cod fillets.

1213
00:50:24,021 --> 00:50:25,389
There was squid too.

1214
00:50:25,455 --> 00:50:26,857
-Yes, the cuttlefish.
-The cuttlefish.

1215
00:50:26,923 --> 00:50:28,658
-He had cuttlefish.
-I soaked the half-dried cuttlefish

1216
00:50:28,725 --> 00:50:29,726
and added cuts before frying it.

1217
00:50:29,793 --> 00:50:32,195
-That must be it.
-Cuttlefish, abalone, and cod.

1218
00:50:33,964 --> 00:50:36,733
I'm so glad our Suk-ku is
enjoying the dish so much.

1219
00:50:36,800 --> 00:50:38,535
Everyone, call him our Suk-ku now.

1220
00:50:38,602 --> 00:50:39,770
-Right.
-Okay.

1221
00:50:40,370 --> 00:50:42,005
-It's so good.
-I see.

1222
00:50:42,973 --> 00:50:46,510
That's wonderful. Next, Reverent Chicken.

1223
00:50:47,277 --> 00:50:50,280
COLD SALAD ABOVE HOT BOWL

1224
00:50:51,214 --> 00:50:55,419
A MIX OF CRUNCHINESS
AND CHEWINESS

1225
00:50:56,686 --> 00:51:00,891
CHEF PARK EUN-YEONG'S
REVERENT CHICKEN

1226
00:51:00,957 --> 00:51:03,060
-Put it next to you.
-Do you eat the bowl too?

1227
00:51:03,126 --> 00:51:05,128
It's usually mixed with sauce.

1228
00:51:05,195 --> 00:51:08,131
-You always do something before you serve.
-He's curious.

1229
00:51:08,198 --> 00:51:11,368
-Chef Edward can't hold his curiosity.
-Kyun.

1230
00:51:11,435 --> 00:51:13,236
-How do I eat this?
-How does he eat this?

1231
00:51:13,303 --> 00:51:16,473
Hold both ends, break it in half,

1232
00:51:16,540 --> 00:51:18,241
then eat the chicken and the topping

1233
00:51:18,308 --> 00:51:21,078
with the noodles in one bite.

1234
00:51:21,144 --> 00:51:23,280
-Break it like this.
-Boldly.

1235
00:51:23,346 --> 00:51:24,748
-Oh.
-Oh.

1236
00:51:24,815 --> 00:51:26,716
WATCHING IN PERSON

1237
00:51:26,783 --> 00:51:28,018
I'll eat it like this.

1238
00:51:28,085 --> 00:51:30,654
You can put everything on that
and take a bite.

1239
00:51:30,720 --> 00:51:34,157
-Different textures and temperatures.
-Like that.

1240
00:51:34,224 --> 00:51:36,326
The textures may feel different.

1241
00:51:36,393 --> 00:51:38,295
He took a good bite.

1242
00:51:38,361 --> 00:51:39,863
CRUNCH

1243
00:51:39,930 --> 00:51:41,331
SAVORING

1244
00:51:41,398 --> 00:51:43,233
Gosh, listen to that sound.

1245
00:51:43,300 --> 00:51:44,668
You have good ears.

1246
00:51:46,336 --> 00:51:48,405
Bong-sik has good ears.

1247
00:51:48,472 --> 00:51:50,474
It looks strange,

1248
00:51:50,540 --> 00:51:53,143
-but anyone will like this taste.
-I see.

1249
00:51:53,210 --> 00:51:54,444
-A taste anyone will like.
-Yes.

1250
00:51:54,511 --> 00:51:55,979
-The geotjeori.
-Just the kimchi.

1251
00:51:56,046 --> 00:51:58,548
She washed the kimchi and stir-fried it.

1252
00:51:58,615 --> 00:52:01,284
I stir-fried it with tomato juice.

1253
00:52:01,852 --> 00:52:04,488
-I love stir-fried kimchi.
-I see.

1254
00:52:04,554 --> 00:52:06,323
What a relief.

1255
00:52:06,389 --> 00:52:08,992
He tries another crunchy bite.

1256
00:52:09,059 --> 00:52:10,427
And some kimchi.

1257
00:52:10,494 --> 00:52:12,829
Is the taste worth his reverence?

1258
00:52:12,896 --> 00:52:14,764
It's really good.

1259
00:52:14,831 --> 00:52:18,101
I wonder if he'll want to revere it.

1260
00:52:19,202 --> 00:52:20,537
So?

1261
00:52:21,638 --> 00:52:23,039
It's fun to eat.

1262
00:52:23,106 --> 00:52:25,275
-It's fun.
-The texture.

1263
00:52:25,342 --> 00:52:27,577
I have to make an action to eat it,

1264
00:52:27,644 --> 00:52:30,213
-putting the chicken on top and all.
-Yes, right.

1265
00:52:30,280 --> 00:52:33,183
-That was delicious.
-I think he's done.

1266
00:52:34,451 --> 00:52:35,986
Okay, then.

1267
00:52:36,052 --> 00:52:39,422
Mr. Hyun Bong-sik is
drooling out of control.

1268
00:52:40,290 --> 00:52:44,060
He'll try a bite too. That one is
Chef Ho-young's Su-Su-Su-Super Udon.

1269
00:52:47,063 --> 00:52:48,498
-Is it good?
-Yes.

1270
00:52:48,565 --> 00:52:49,833
How is it?

1271
00:52:49,900 --> 00:52:52,435
Both the texture and the taste are

1272
00:52:52,502 --> 00:52:57,374
polarized, just as he wanted.

1273
00:52:57,440 --> 00:53:02,279
If this was sold somewhere,
I'd eat it every day.

1274
00:53:02,345 --> 00:53:03,880
THE BEST COMPLIMENT EVER

1275
00:53:03,947 --> 00:53:06,249
He'd eat it every day
if it were available.

1276
00:53:06,650 --> 00:53:07,884
SLURP

1277
00:53:07,951 --> 00:53:10,320
If Bong-sik had to choose someone,

1278
00:53:10,387 --> 00:53:12,556
Chef Ho-young could've won.

1279
00:53:12,622 --> 00:53:14,424
He finishes the soup too.

1280
00:53:14,925 --> 00:53:17,460
I'm sorry to ask,
but were you quite hungry?

1281
00:53:18,128 --> 00:53:19,796
-It's really good.
-Is it?

1282
00:53:19,863 --> 00:53:21,531
He finished it because it was good.

1283
00:53:21,598 --> 00:53:24,768
And next, Reverent Chicken.

1284
00:53:25,969 --> 00:53:29,706
The crunch sound is amazing.

1285
00:53:29,773 --> 00:53:31,308
-Do you like it?
-Right.

1286
00:53:31,374 --> 00:53:34,811
You could work as a judge somewhere.
You have great facial expressions.

1287
00:53:34,878 --> 00:53:36,379
-Gosh.
-My gosh.

1288
00:53:36,446 --> 00:53:37,447
I'm so glad I came today.

1289
00:53:37,514 --> 00:53:39,216
Thanks for inviting me, Suk-ku.

1290
00:53:40,083 --> 00:53:43,119
All right. It's the moment of truth.

1291
00:53:43,186 --> 00:53:46,723
Both Jung Ho-young and Park Eun-yeong
have not lost a single time yet.

1292
00:53:46,790 --> 00:53:50,227
Whose dish did Suk-ku enjoy more?

1293
00:53:50,293 --> 00:53:51,828
Number one for Jung Ho-young,

1294
00:53:51,895 --> 00:53:53,730
and number two for Park Eun-yeong.

1295
00:53:53,797 --> 00:53:55,532
Please make your decision

1296
00:53:55,599 --> 00:53:57,867
and press the button!

1297
00:53:58,902 --> 00:53:59,903
I did.

1298
00:53:59,970 --> 00:54:02,472
He just pushed the button.

1299
00:54:02,539 --> 00:54:05,809
Round "I revere polar opposites."

1300
00:54:05,875 --> 00:54:08,245
Both chefs have two stars.

1301
00:54:08,311 --> 00:54:10,146
Who'll take place
as the joint first place?

1302
00:54:10,213 --> 00:54:13,049
Will it be Jung Ho-young
or Park Eun-yeong?

1303
00:54:13,116 --> 00:54:15,885
Who did Suk-ku choose?

1304
00:54:15,952 --> 00:54:18,188
Show us the result!

1305
00:54:18,255 --> 00:54:19,556
Who won?

1306
00:54:21,291 --> 00:54:22,292
Suk-ku's choice!

1307
00:54:24,194 --> 00:54:26,196
CHEF PARK EUN-YEONG'S
REVERENT CHICKEN WINS

1308
00:54:26,263 --> 00:54:29,799
It was Chef Eun-yeong.
Chef Eun-yeong wins.

1309
00:54:29,866 --> 00:54:30,867
Thank you.

1310
00:54:30,934 --> 00:54:32,636
PARK EUN-YEONG
CONTINUES WITHOUT LOSING

1311
00:54:32,702 --> 00:54:34,371
Why did you choose Chef Eun-yeong?

1312
00:54:34,437 --> 00:54:37,574
When it came to my personal preference

1313
00:54:37,641 --> 00:54:40,143
and the level of completion,

1314
00:54:40,210 --> 00:54:43,780
Chef Ho-young's dishes were more pleasing.

1315
00:54:43,847 --> 00:54:46,149
But I've never seen anything like that.

1316
00:54:46,216 --> 00:54:50,287
When she brought in
the difference in textures,

1317
00:54:50,353 --> 00:54:55,659
I liked how she showed
a bit more creativity in that way.

1318
00:54:55,725 --> 00:54:56,726
I see.

1319
00:54:56,793 --> 00:54:58,628
CREATIVITY DECIDED THE MATCH

1320
00:54:58,695 --> 00:55:00,263
This means

1321
00:55:00,330 --> 00:55:04,467
Chef Eun-yeong is now first place
with Chef Hyun-suk.

1322
00:55:04,534 --> 00:55:08,938
This is her third win in a row.
Suk-ku will put a star on Chef Eun-yeong.

1323
00:55:09,005 --> 00:55:12,342
She becomes the joint first place!
Congratulations!

1324
00:55:12,409 --> 00:55:15,278
-Thank you!
-My gosh, Park Eun-yeong!

1325
00:55:15,779 --> 00:55:20,717
PARK EUN-YEONG'S
REVERENT CHICKEN

1326
00:55:20,784 --> 00:55:25,155
<i>The second round</i>
<i>with ingredients from Suk-ku's fridge.</i>

1327
00:55:25,221 --> 00:55:27,290
We finally have

1328
00:55:27,357 --> 00:55:31,494
the return match of the final round
of <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>.

1329
00:55:31,561 --> 00:55:34,564
The first place of <i>Culinary Class Wars,</i>
Chef Kwon Sung-jun,

1330
00:55:34,631 --> 00:55:38,802
is up against the second place,
Chef Edward Lee.

1331
00:55:38,868 --> 00:55:42,405
Many people enjoyed their battle,

1332
00:55:42,472 --> 00:55:46,076
and many others awaited
their return match.

1333
00:55:46,142 --> 00:55:50,513
And that match came to reality
here on <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

1334
00:55:51,214 --> 00:55:52,215
All right.

1335
00:55:52,282 --> 00:55:54,250
STRETCHING

1336
00:55:54,317 --> 00:55:55,919
We need to make a note of this.

1337
00:55:55,985 --> 00:55:57,887
He's stretching.

1338
00:55:57,954 --> 00:55:59,622
-What are you doing?
-He's stretching.

1339
00:55:59,689 --> 00:56:01,458
This isn't ultimate fighting.

1340
00:56:01,524 --> 00:56:03,026
He's suddenly stretching.

1341
00:56:03,093 --> 00:56:06,830
Chef Kyun and Chef Sung-jun are
both warming up right now.

1342
00:56:06,896 --> 00:56:09,499
They must be nervous.

1343
00:56:09,566 --> 00:56:11,468
Yes, they're stretching.

1344
00:56:11,534 --> 00:56:12,869
This is the return match.

1345
00:56:14,070 --> 00:56:16,806
Although I won <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>,

1346
00:56:16,873 --> 00:56:21,544
-Chef Edward took a lot of my spotlight.
-Yes.

1347
00:56:21,611 --> 00:56:25,615
So I was also a bit worried
that he'd take attention away from me.

1348
00:56:26,816 --> 00:56:28,952
Yes, that must feel unfair.

1349
00:56:29,018 --> 00:56:30,920
He lost his attention to Edward.

1350
00:56:30,987 --> 00:56:33,356
Edward Lee took everyone's love,

1351
00:56:33,423 --> 00:56:35,825
although he was the first place.

1352
00:56:35,892 --> 00:56:38,361
This is now our third match,

1353
00:56:38,428 --> 00:56:41,464
and I think it'll be
the most nerve-racking and serious one.

1354
00:56:41,531 --> 00:56:46,336
Recently, I received
so much love from Korea,

1355
00:56:46,403 --> 00:56:47,771
and it made me so happy.

1356
00:56:47,837 --> 00:56:50,573
But today, I don't need any love.

1357
00:56:50,640 --> 00:56:52,909
-Revenge.
-Revenge!

1358
00:56:52,976 --> 00:56:54,477
-Gosh, he doesn't need love.
-I see.

1359
00:56:54,544 --> 00:56:56,613
-What he needs today is revenge.
-Revenge.

1360
00:56:56,679 --> 00:56:58,181
That was all he waited for.

1361
00:56:58,248 --> 00:56:59,883
A return match.

1362
00:56:59,949 --> 00:57:01,785
-It's literally his revenge.
-Yes.

1363
00:57:01,851 --> 00:57:05,021
Chef Sung-jun, you won against Edward Lee.

1364
00:57:05,088 --> 00:57:07,424
What do you think is your secret?

1365
00:57:07,490 --> 00:57:09,559
I honestly had only one way of winning.

1366
00:57:09,626 --> 00:57:11,594
-What is it?
-I chose the safe path.

1367
00:57:11,661 --> 00:57:13,563
-The safe path.
-The safe path.

1368
00:57:13,630 --> 00:57:15,031
-What he's good at.
-But Chef Edward

1369
00:57:15,098 --> 00:57:16,866
-challenged himself.
-I see.

1370
00:57:16,933 --> 00:57:20,036
But today, let me choose
to challenge myself.

1371
00:57:21,070 --> 00:57:22,071
And Chef Edward?

1372
00:57:22,739 --> 00:57:24,741
But that is

1373
00:57:24,808 --> 00:57:27,677
the style of my cooking.

1374
00:57:28,378 --> 00:57:32,315
-I can't make any safe dishes.
-I see.

1375
00:57:32,382 --> 00:57:33,383
I just…

1376
00:57:35,051 --> 00:57:36,719
-He always challenges himself.
-He does.

1377
00:57:36,786 --> 00:57:39,055
He can't resort
to something he always does.

1378
00:57:39,122 --> 00:57:40,623
He keeps challenging himself.

1379
00:57:40,690 --> 00:57:42,459
I can't believe I'm seeing this.

1380
00:57:42,525 --> 00:57:44,527
Suk-ku, you get to decide the winner
of the return match

1381
00:57:44,594 --> 00:57:46,529
between the first and second places
of <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>.

1382
00:57:46,596 --> 00:57:48,097
-Tell me about it.
-And watch it too.

1383
00:57:48,164 --> 00:57:50,834
-This is crazy.
-My goodness.

1384
00:57:50,900 --> 00:57:55,805
Suk-ku, you need to be
both Ahn Sung-jae and Paik Jong-won.

1385
00:57:55,872 --> 00:57:57,607
No one will protest.

1386
00:57:58,441 --> 00:58:00,610
CHEF SUNG-JUN'S INGREDIENTS: STEVIA
CHERRY TOMATOES, TOMATO BASIL SAUCE

1387
00:58:00,677 --> 00:58:02,812
CHICKEN CURRY, STEAK SAUCE, RICOTTA,
FROZEN BONE SOUP, TRUFFLE OIL AND MORE

1388
00:58:02,879 --> 00:58:06,049
Chef Sung-jun, what's your dish called?

1389
00:58:06,683 --> 00:58:08,084
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

1390
00:58:08,151 --> 00:58:11,054
-Where are you going?
-He must've prepared something.

1391
00:58:11,120 --> 00:58:12,322
Why are you all so prepared?

1392
00:58:13,189 --> 00:58:15,692
A PINK UKULELE?

1393
00:58:15,758 --> 00:58:17,861
-A ukulele?
-You prepared something!

1394
00:58:17,927 --> 00:58:19,629
He's serious about this.

1395
00:58:20,363 --> 00:58:21,965
He's a good singer.

1396
00:58:22,031 --> 00:58:23,700
-My dish is called…
-Yes?

1397
00:58:23,766 --> 00:58:26,069
FULL OF EXPECTATIONS

1398
00:58:26,135 --> 00:58:29,205
<i>Your Perilla Leaf Scent</i>

1399
00:58:30,039 --> 00:58:32,675
<i>in the Gnocchi</i>

1400
00:58:32,742 --> 00:58:34,944
A PERFECT FINISH

1401
00:58:36,112 --> 00:58:38,114
Your Perilla Leaf Scent in the Gnocchi.

1402
00:58:38,181 --> 00:58:40,283
Gnocchi. He's making gnocchi.

1403
00:58:40,350 --> 00:58:43,620
I planned on making fresh pasta
for the battle

1404
00:58:43,686 --> 00:58:45,922
I knew I shouldn't lose.

1405
00:58:45,989 --> 00:58:48,424
So I'll make the dough right away

1406
00:58:48,491 --> 00:58:52,295
-The dough?
-and make gnocchi with ricotta cheese.

1407
00:58:52,362 --> 00:58:53,863
It's gnocchi with ricotta cheese.

1408
00:58:53,930 --> 00:58:55,798
-What? With ricotta?
-That's my plan.

1409
00:58:55,865 --> 00:58:58,735
I thought of Suk-ku's story

1410
00:58:58,801 --> 00:59:01,671
and make a sauce that fits
the Art Institute of Chicago.

1411
00:59:01,738 --> 00:59:06,943
When I think of that university,
it's probably a place with mixed culture…

1412
00:59:07,010 --> 00:59:09,312
-Yes.
-…with artistic people.

1413
00:59:09,379 --> 00:59:11,347
I'll throw in curry from India,

1414
00:59:11,414 --> 00:59:13,216
salsa from Mexico,

1415
00:59:13,283 --> 00:59:15,685
and ragu from Italy.

1416
00:59:15,752 --> 00:59:19,622
I want to try making a multicultural dish.

1417
00:59:19,689 --> 00:59:22,225
There's always cilantro in salsa, right?

1418
00:59:22,292 --> 00:59:24,928
-I'm using perilla leaves instead.
-Perilla leaves.

1419
00:59:24,994 --> 00:59:27,997
Also, I'm putting perilla leaves
into the gnocchi.

1420
00:59:28,064 --> 00:59:30,533
-In the gnocchi.
-In everything.

1421
00:59:30,600 --> 00:59:34,537
-In the dough.
-I'll make a literal perilla leaf party.

1422
00:59:34,604 --> 00:59:36,873
-I see.
-Everything is perilla leaf.

1423
00:59:36,940 --> 00:59:41,377
Yes, and look at his eyes.
They're menacing.

1424
00:59:41,444 --> 00:59:44,213
-And he isn't joking around.
-No.

1425
00:59:45,048 --> 00:59:48,952
CHEF EDWARD'S INGREDIENTS:
TENDERLOIN, STRIP LOIN, GEOTJEORI

1426
00:59:49,018 --> 00:59:52,922
LEMON JUICE, MILK, NOODLES,
SSAMJANG, PERILLA LEAF

1427
00:59:52,989 --> 00:59:55,258
What's your dish called?

1428
00:59:55,325 --> 00:59:56,526
I prepared

1429
00:59:56,593 --> 00:59:58,361
Wrap

1430
00:59:58,428 --> 01:00:02,732
More Beautiful Than Paradise.

1431
01:00:03,766 --> 01:00:05,735
He throws in a performance.

1432
01:00:05,802 --> 01:00:08,605
-Wrap More Beautiful Than Paradise.
-Wrap More Beautiful Than Paradise.

1433
01:00:09,172 --> 01:00:10,506
A BIG PERFORMER, EDDY

1434
01:00:10,573 --> 01:00:11,975
He has great performances.

